title: Your company doesn't give a shit about good software design
published: true
---

Interfaces, Polymorphism, Design Patterns, SOLID Design principles, writing code that is scalable and extendable - why do we care so much about all of this stuff? Because we think that good software design matters - it is what distinguishes mediocre software engineers from great ones. And being recognized as a great software engineer within your company will lead to both fame and fortune.

> Flash news - Your company doesn't give a shit about good software design


